The General Manager, Public Relations, Nigeria Meteorological Agency, Muntari Ibrahim, was yesterday kidnapped  along the Kaduna-Abuja Road. His son, Ibrahim,  said his father,  along with his brother, Tasi’u Isah, were returning to Abuja when they were abducted. He said the kidnappers came in two cars with the first blocking the front that forced his father’s official car, a Peugeot 408, to stop. “The gunmen shot in the air before whisking the victim away. They have not yet reached out to us “ he added. Daily Trust reports that Muntari is still recuperating from the injury sustained in a motor accident that happened last year. ‎ Gunmen kidnap top NiMet official NiMet, India to collaborate on data sharing UniAbuja staff kidnapped in Kaduna